-- South Africa Stocks: Cipla Medpro, Datatec Move in Johannesburg
-- B y   R o b e r t   B r a n d
-- 2012-03-15T08:29:25Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-15/south-africa-stocks-cipla-medpro-datatec-move-in-johannesburg.html
The  FTSE/JSE Africa All Share Index (JALSH) 
advanced for a third day, gaining 0.2 percent to 34,492.54 as of
10:27 a.m. in Johannesburg, a record on a closing basis.  The following are among the most active equities in the
South African market today. Stock symbols follow company names.  Cipla Medpro South Africa Ltd. (CMP)  , a generic-drug
manufacturer, declined for the first time in three days after
saying its anti-retroviral tender business didn’t “materialize
to the numbers we expected.” The shares dropped 1.8 percent to
6.65 rand.  Datatec Ltd. (DTC)  , a Johannesburg-based computer-
services company, gained for a fourth day, adding 0.9 percent to
45.23 rand. The company said earnings for the year through
February will be in line with forecasts published during 2011.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Robert Brand in  Cape Town  at 
 rbrand9@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
